---
By: Hugh of Saint-Victor
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 261
    Verse: 5
Tags:
  - Ignorance
---
Ignorant and foolish men, with a labor as vain as it is obstinate, search
out the natures of things while they remain in ignorance of the One who is
the Author and Maker of themselves and of all things alike.
